   <text type="translation">
      <body>
         <pb facs="1866_01_03_Kniffler_Nagasaki_von_B_Telge_Shanghai_1.tif" n="1"/>
         <p>B. TELGE<lb/> Shanghai, 3rd January 1867[?]<lb/>Messrs. L. Kniffler
                +Co<lb/>Nagasaki<lb/>I received your esteemed letter from <lb/>28th December, which
                handed me[?] a parcel-ticket and<lb/>2 packages[?], which I have just correctly
                received. <lb/>I hardly think that anything can be done <lb/>with regard to the
                rifles, but I will offer them to the <lb/>government and can then let Mr. Sander
                know <lb/>more details. Unfortunately it is already too late today <lb/>to be able
                to give you accurate rates for different<lb/>samples of ginseng, these will
                follow<lb/>at the next opportunity. <lb/>With kindest thanks for your friendly
                <lb/>wishes for the New Year <lb/>I return these best wishes wholeheartedly,
                <lb/>Yours sincerely and respectfully <lb/>B. Telge</p>
         <pb facs="1866_01_03_Kniffler_Nagasaki_von_B_Telge_Shanghai_2.tif" n="2"/>
         <pb facs="1866_01_03_Kniffler_Nagasaki_von_B_Telge_Shanghai_3.tif" n="3"/>
         <pb facs="1866_01_03_Kniffler_Nagasaki_von_B_Telge_Shanghai_4.tif" n="envelope"/>
         <p>per “Pembroken”<lb/>Messrs. L. Kniffler + Co<lb/>Nagasaki<lb/>⟨1866<lb/>Shanghai 3rd
                Jan<lb/>B. Telge<lb/>R[eceived on] 6 Jan⟩</p>
      </body>
